Checklist for the time when a new version is about to be released:

0.1 change BackTrack by Backtrack everywhere?
0.3 Add some functions from file: addthesefunctions 
0.4 Make some changes from ToDo list. 
--
1.  check spelling.
2.  check examples.
3.  check comments match examples: '<!-- RandomComment -->'.
    --> grep RandomComment *.xml ../lib/*.gd
4.  check version number
5.  check release date.
6.  check citation info.
7.  remove disclaimer in preface.
8.  build the manual.
9.  clean up backup files.
10. commit changes.
11. push to git repository.
12. pull from webpage
    --> make 
13. update webpage
14. alert on yagsnews@xamanek.izt.uam.mx (and others?)